AIA.caption: a time frame has been selected
AIA.name: select

AIC.caption: an event's start or end time has been modified
AIC.name: timeschanged

ARi.caption: Body clicked outside of moveable group
ARi.name: body_clicked_outside_of_moveable_group

AYb.caption: a day has been clicked
AYb.doc: good for picking a date to show times
AYb.name: dayclicked

AfX.caption: A Calendar Skeleton Has Been Rendered
AfX.name: skeleton_rendered

Afa.caption: Calendar's JS has finished being ran
Afa.name: calendarready

AIG.caption: Event Start Times
AIG.doc: dates should be formatted using the extended ISO format
AIG.name: start_list

AIH.caption: Event End Times
AIH.doc: dates should be formatted using the extended ISO format
AIH.name: end_list

AII.caption: Event Titles
AII.doc: Be mindful of titles with commas and change the delimiter accordingly.  IF YOUR TITLE HAS A COMMA, YOU BETTER WELL CHANGE the delimiter below TO AVOID BREAKING THE APP## is always a nice option for delimiter as it is incredibly unlikely to occur in everyday texts..                       _________________________________________________________                                  When you have to change the dlimiter, you do it by using the operator :format as text. then for each item for the list you would use 'this word' as the item and then set your delimiter. whatever you set as the delimiter here you need to copy into the box below. check out the videos on this plugins notion page to see more about this feature. access the notion by going to the plugin page and clicking through.
AII.name: title_list

AIJ.caption: Event ID's
AIJ.doc: If events are coming from the DB, you will use the uniqueID from the DB.  the google calendar events also have their own eventID's be sure to use these if you have any chance in hell of completing CRUD actions on your events instead of just READING them only
AIJ.name: unique_id_list

AIK.caption: Event Color List
AIK.doc: now, this following field is totally optional. but odds are you want to use discrete colors for events based on who they're with or what they're related to.  so, the only caveat pain in the ass is that you will need to :format as text each list you want to use without option. each list will need to use the tilde ~ as the delimiter. this allows you to not worry about hex vs RGB formatting for event colors which will allow you to accept colors from most any data source. sorry, but it works better this way. :)what color should the event be? All event color lists should be ":format as text" with context to show per item as the bubble choice "This text" and the delimiter as a tilde "~" . join each data source list with a tilde '~'. this allows you to not worry about hex vs rgb for your event colors. heck, you can even use rgba color codes. _______________________________________________ remeber. you dont HAVE to use this, but you'd be a lot cooler if you did!
AIK.name: color_list

AIL.caption: Event Editable List
AIL.doc: this applies to discrete events. do you want this to be able to be dragged/resized easily. requires a manual data modification. see the popup in the plugin example. takes lists of true false values separated by commas
AIL.name: editable

AIM.caption: Event Identifier List
AIM.doc: Additional property to give the event. can be used to control workflows
AIM.name: whatami

AIN.caption: All fields below should be lists of equal length. You can add additional lists of events by separating the data sources with the appropriate delimiter. be mindful that many lists use a comma as a delimiter. That's fine until the content of your list also has a comma such as in a long text or this text you are reading. If that is the case, you will want to :format as text your list, and simply use a tilde as the delimiter.
AIN.name: all_fields_below_should_be_lists_of_equal_length._you_can_add_additional_lists_of_events_by_separating_the_data_sources_with_a_comma

AIO.caption: Clicked Event Data
AIO.doc: must be set to this: Clicked Event Data
AIO.name: event_data

AIQ.caption: _____________________________________________________    Exposed Event States   _____________________________________________________ Please be sure to set these correctly.You should be ableto simply click the drop down and begin to type the name ofthe property itself. When you find the matching name in the dropdown, select that item. These are used to expose various types of data from the calendar element. There's a lot you can get out of it, some of it redundant, so be sure to check out the gitbook page to see more info about these and all of the available properties.
AIQ.doc: You must set these. The following two options are not settings or data inputs. Instead this is how you get information about events from the calendar. read the documentation for each to identify how to set them.  the first option will output data when you click on an event.

AQB.caption: Title Color - Light
AQB.doc: . This calendar element will automagically set your event text color based on the darkness of the event. So, pick a light color and a dark color and the calendar will pick which to use for you!  This allows for a wider array of event colors to be used.
AQB.name: lightcolor

AQC.caption: Title Color - Dark
AQC.doc: . This calendar element will automagically set your event text color based on the darkness of the event. So, pick a light color and a dark color and the calendar will pick which to use for you!  This allows for a wider array of event colors to be used.
AQC.name: darkcolor

ARC.caption: Modified Event Data
ARC.doc: must be set to this: Modified Event Data
ARC.name: modified_event_data

ARJ.caption: Event Location List
ARJ.doc: include your event locations here. separate each data source with your chosen delimiter
ARJ.name: event_location

ARK.caption: Event Prop 1 List
ARK.doc: Any kind of extra information formatted as text.
ARK.name: extra_property_1

ARQ.caption: _____________________________________________________ Required Information  _____________________________________________________
ARQ.doc: the following 6 properties are non-negotiable meaning that if you dont fill them out, you wont get events to display on your calendar. Be sure to read the documentatino for each property.
ARQ.name: -----------------------------event_times_--------------------------

ARV.caption: :format as text delimiter
ARV.doc: many of your fields may have commas in their text fields. for example, color in an RGBA(0,0,0,0) format. if this is the case in ANY of your input fields, you should use the operater :format as text on the list, using whatever delimiter you choose here other than a comma. most often setting it to a double hash '##' or a single tilde '~' would work just fine   _____________________________________________________ TO BE CLEAR, IT MAY BE EASIER FOR YOU TO SIMPLY :FIND AND REPLACE ANY COMMA IN A TEXT FIELD. IF YOU MUST MODIFY THIS, YOU WOULD NEED TO ;FORMAT AS TEXT ALL YOUR LIST FIELDS TO USE THIS NEW DELIMITER. IT'S A PAIN IN THE BUT BUT IF YOU DESIRE COMMAS IN YOUR EVENT DATA, FOR NOW THIS IS HOW WE'LL DO IT.
ARV.name: unidelim

ARW.caption: _____________________________________________________  setup Event Editability  _____________________________________________________
ARW.doc: these settings allow you to control how to determine the editabiltiy of an event. this means the ability for events to be modified once they are created either through drag/dropping or stretching the time on the calendar. this can also be used in workflow  logic to prevent event deletion. ____________________________________________    You can control them by haing a true/false value associated with each event or you can control all events on the calendar together.
ARW.name: ----------_customize_the_editability_of_events_-------

ARX.caption: How many events to modify
ARX.doc: the default choice is to edit all events 'editability' together. Choose 1. You can either set each events editable property independently or you can set them all together.  if you choose 'all together' be mindful of the next setting. all events will be editable by default.
ARX.name: editableindividualortogether
ARX.options: all of them together,each discrete event

ARY.caption: Allow Event Edits
ARY.doc: check this box if you want events editable. leave the box unchecked for events to not be editable
ARY.name: all_events_editable

ARg.caption: Event Prop 2 List
ARg.doc: Any kind of extra information formatted as text.
ARg.name: extra_property_2

ASf.caption: Event Resource List
ASf.doc: this list needs to be the same length as all other event input fields.
ASf.name: eventresources

ASl.caption: Data Out
ASl.doc: fringe use case. if you ever get a circular error while referencing the calendars dates to produce data for the calendar you may need this. more data out will get added over time.
ASl.name: check_me_if_you_want_to_use_me

AUY.caption: Viewing Time Zone
AUY.doc: use this to display dates/times appropriately! It should say America/Kalamazoo but...... If you're like me, your town wont work outta the box. you'll likely need to identify your own timezone ID.
AUY.name: timezoneid

AUc.caption: Cross Day Bkgrnd Color
AUc.doc: this specifically refers to in the monthgrid view, when an event extends a 24 hour period, what color should that events background be as it will span the days it consumes.
AUc.name: event_background_color

AUg.caption: First Day of the Week
AUg.doc: The default value depends on the current locale.  The value must be a number that represents the day of the week.  Sunday=0, Monday=1, Tuesday=2, etc.
AUg.name: first_day_of_the_week

AUn.caption: Assign Color from Identifier
AUn.doc: in the boxes below you should assign event names and colors. The Event Type field is directly associated with the Event Identifier field. So. if you dont use identifiers,  all colors will be the default event color chosen above.
AUn.name: useeventspecificcolors

AVA.caption: Resource Label Font Size
AVA.doc: This field  will take any appropriate CSS font size. you may find that with more than a few resources, you'd like to be able to decrease the font size a little bit.
AVA.name: fontsizeresources

AVR.caption: Background Color
AVR.doc: well, incase you weren't ready or didn't set up your DB for colors yet, choose your default event color here!
AVR.name: defaulteventcolor

AVZ.caption: Default Color
AVZ.doc: yes. here's another default color box. it's for convinience. know that you need to set this if you are coloring events based on their identifiers.
AVZ.name: default_color_based_on_identifier

AVe.caption: Filter Eventless Resources
AVe.doc: When this setting is activated, only resources that have associated events will be displayed. When activated, please be aware that in order for resources to render, event data will need to finish being fetched. this setting only applies to the current view.
AVe.name: filterresourceview

AVf.caption: Assign 'no Resource'
AVf.doc: if you havent provided a resource name, the calendar can provide a default. this lets you create events that can then be moved on to any open resources timeslots. alternatively, you could choose not to do this and use the ability to filter events without resources.
AVf.name: assignresource

AVg.caption: _____________________________________________________   Link Event Color to Event Identifier   __________________________________________________
AVg.doc: using these will set color based on the event type instead of based on the list from above.  clicking in the box below will negate your list of colors above.  if there is enough need we  may be able to make the two work in harmony or be dynamic. well, it is dynamic. so at anytime you can swictch on and off the box below and this will update the event colors accordingly.  do it based on the view.
AVg.name: based_on_event_identifier

AWC.caption: Time Slot format
AWC.doc: takes any moment.js time format string (h:mm a) is my preferred format but the bosnian language (among others) doesn't like this format with the current javascript library so here you go. decide your time format and add your own signifier for before or after noon. ..... There are so many ways to format this. go here https://devhints.io/moment  . scroll down a little bit and look at the table for Time formatting.
AWC.name: timeslotformat

AWD.caption: Timeslot Custom AM
AWD.doc: if you want to customize the look of your AM/PM, be sure to leave the option off from the setting above.
AWD.name: customam

AWG.caption: Display All day slot?
AWG.doc: check me to display the all day slot at the top of the calendar.
AWG.name: alldayslot

AWJ.caption: Custom Day name list
AWJ.doc: start with your sunday. if you include a list here, it will automatically override the standard day names. this is useful when you're language is properly supported.
AWJ.name: daynames

AWK.caption: Date Column format
AWK.doc: the day header format will accept a moment.js string here. this is only relevant when you are not customizing day names. this is any acceptable moment.js  format string for dates
AWK.name: momentjsformat

AWL.caption: Date w/ Custom Day Name
AWL.doc: when you are using a  custom day name list, you can also choose to display the date next to the day name. this follows the date column format entered above and will insert that to the right of the day name you enter.
AWL.name: include_date_with_day

AWO.caption: Visible
AWO.doc: This can be used with the output of visibiity from the Data Helper welement. if you dont load the calendar visibliy on the screen there's a chance events dont show. this fixes that.  Essentially if you use the visible property, when you return to the tab it forces a reload of the calendar on the screen but since it's unlikely no data changed, the DB isnt called.
AWO.name: visible

AWc.caption: Calendar Language
AWc.doc: this field accepts any valid locale code. jaredgibb.bubbleapps.io/timeslottester has a list of most accepted locale codes.
AWc.name: locale

AZi.caption: Restrict Event Drag-and-Dropping
AZi.doc: Restrict Event Drag-and-Dropping. Limits event dragging and resizing to certain windows of time
AZi.name: restrict_dragresizing_to_business_hours_only

AZj.caption: Daily Start Time
AZj.doc: takes time in a 24:00 hour format
AZj.name: restricted_selection_start_time

AZk.caption: Daily End Time
AZk.doc: takes time in a 24:00 hour format
AZk.name: restricted_selection_end_time

AZl.caption: Applicable Days
AZl.doc: days of week. a list of zero-based day of week integers (0=Sunday).
AZl.name: restricted_selection_days_of_week

AZv.caption: Applicable Days
AZv.doc: this field takes a list of numbers 0-6
AZv.name: bdays_of_the_week

AZy.caption: Allow Time Selection
AZy.doc: This blocks the selection of any timefram on the calendar. good to use if you only want users to be able to select events. can be used to remove confusion in these cases as a user WONT wonder why they are able to select a time frame
AZy.name: allow_free_selection

AaA.caption: Title Date Format
AaA.doc: Use any momentJS format string. https://momentjs.com/docs/#/displaying/
AaA.name: titleformatmomentjs

AaB.caption: Left Nav Button
AaB.doc: should probably be any of the following: timeGridDay,timelineDay,resourceTimelineDay,resourceDayGridDay,resourceTimeGridDay                 The reality is that you can use any of the button texts in any of these three slots. it just makes sense to keep a little standardization but not always!
AaB.name: leftbutton

AaC.caption: Middle Nav Button
AaC.doc: should be any of the following: resourceDayGridWeek,timeGridWeek,timelineWeek,resourceTimeGridWeek,resourceTimelineWeek,dayGridWeek,listDay,listWeek,
AaC.name: middlebutton

AaD.caption: Right Nav Button
AaD.doc: should be any of the following: resourceTimelineMonth,dayGridMonth,resourceDayGridMonth, dayGridDaylistMonth, listYear
AaD.name: rightbutton

AaH.caption: Font Size
AaH.doc: Change the event font size here. You can use any appropriate css value herer
AaH.name: eventfontsize

AaQ.caption: Selected TimeFrame
AaQ.doc: must be set to this: Selected TimeFrame Data
AaQ.name: selected_timeframe

Aae.caption: Calendar Data
Aae.doc: mustbe set to this: Calendar Data
Aae.name: calendar_data

Ads.caption: Border Color
Ads.doc: guess what. this can be a list or a singular color if you really want it to be! just try.  BUT if you use a list, be sure to separate with  a tilde the exact same at the Event Colors LIst!  leave this blank to make sure that your events are a solid color (no border)
Ads.name: bordercolorlist

Aff.caption: Hour Format
Aff.doc: If the time were 6:05 'numeric' would produce something like 6 '2-digit' would produce something like 06
Aff.name: event_hour

Afg.caption: Minute Format
Afg.doc: If the time were 6:05 'numeric' would produce something like 5 '2-digit' would produce something like 05
Afg.name: event_minute

Afh.caption: Omit 0-Minute
Afh.doc: if true, times like 6:00 will display as 6
Afh.name: omit0minute

Afi.caption: Meridiem
Afi.doc: Normally with a 12-hour clock the meridiem displays as A.M./P.M. 'lowercase' will force it to display like a.m./p.m. 'short' will force it to display like am/pm 'narrow' will force it to display like a/p false will prevent it from displaying altogether
Afi.name: meridiem

Afj.caption: 12 or 24 hr format
Afj.doc: true for a 12-hour clock, false for a 24-hour clock
Afj.name: hour12

Afk.caption: Minimum Snap Duration
Afk.doc: The time interval at which a dragged event will snap to the time axis. Also affects the granularity at which selections can be made.             a string in the format hh:mm:ss.sss, hh:mm:sss or hh:mm. For example, '05:00' signifies 5 hours. a total number of milliseconds
Afk.name: snapduration

AgK.caption: Resource Order
AgK.doc: Can be a single Resource property name. The resources will be ordered ascendingly by the value of this property.  If prefixed with a minus sign like '-propertyName', the ordering will be descending.  Compound ordering criteria can be specified as a single string separated by commas. (your options are title,prop1,prop2 )
AgK.name: resourceorder

AgL.caption: Resource Group List
AgL.doc: these are properties of the resources listed in the 'specific resource list' wayyyyyy above. this should be a list of groupings specific the resource. if the resource does not belong group, it's entry should be blank.  this value should come from the same list of values you used to set the specific resource list. NOT THE EVENT RESOURCE LISTB entry that your
AgL.name: resourcegroups

AgM.caption: Resource  Prop 1 List
AgM.doc: this should be a list of properties specific the resource. if the resource does not belong group, it's entry should be blank
AgM.name: resource_grp__prop_1

AgN.caption: Resource  Prop 2 List
AgN.doc: this should be a list of properties specific the resource. if the resource does not belong group, it's entry should be blank
AgN.name: resource_grp__prop_2

AgO.caption: Resource Column Label
AgO.doc: What text do you want displayed across the top of the resource column
AgO.name: resourcelabeltext

AgP.caption: the No Group Name
AgP.doc: A standard grouping for resources that dont have a group
AgP.name: nogroupname

AgQ.caption: Use Grouping
AgQ.doc: Awesome. you've made it this far. this means you want to group resources by some common value. set this to YES to make sure you can group. know some things first.  SO >->->->->->->->->->->->->->    first things first. know that The 3 columns should correlate exactly with your Specific resource list. in fact, these next three fields shouuld come from your resource itself. in fact, if you got your resrouce name from some object in the DB, the group that it belongs to should be found in the same resource object. same for propr 1 and prop 2.   think about it this way. you are simly grabbing another piece of data from the rows you got your specific resources. so if they are filtered/ordered, etc, the same must be done here for the following 3 inputs.
AgQ.name: usegroups

AiS.caption: Calendar Min Time
AiS.doc: The default "00:00:00" means the start time will be at the very beginning of the day (midnight).  Determines the first time slot, even when the scrollbars have been scrolled all the way back.
AiS.name: initstarttime

AiT.caption: Calendar Max Time
AiT.doc: The default "24:00:00" means the end time will be at the very end of the day (midnight).  Determines the last slot, even when the scrollbars have been scrolled all the way back.
AiT.name: initendtime

AiV.caption: Initial Scroll Time
AiV.doc: Determines how far forward the scroll pane is initially scrolled.  Duration, default: '06:00:00' (6am) The user will be able to scroll back to see events before this time. If you want to prevent users from doing this, use the minTime option instead.
AiV.name: initscrolltime

AiY.caption: Initial Calendar View
AiY.doc: you can use any of the following for this. timeGridDay,timeGridWeek,timelineDay,timelineWeek,dayGridDay,dayGridWeek,dayGridMonth,listDay,listWeek,listMonth,listYear,customView1,customView2,resourceTimeGridDay,resourceTimeGridWeek,resourceDayGridMonth,resourceDayGridDay,resourceDayGridWeek,resourceTimelineDay,resourceTimelineWeek,resourceTimelineMonth. if you try to initialize a calendar without this being loaded which could happen if you load the calendar and load this value from the db, it will likely cause issues. make  sure this value is availabel before loading the calendar, not after. so, you probably wouldnt load the calendar on page load, you'd want to keep it hidden until the state holding this value is available. .
AiY.name: initcalendar_view

Aii.caption: initheaders
Aii.doc: If this is unchecked, you will need to use bubble  elements to create navigation buttons and a month text Display
Aii.name: initheaders

Aij.caption: Button Icons
Aij.doc: Do you want icons for your navigation buttons?
Aij.name: initbuttonicons

AjG.caption: Resource Area Size
AjG.doc: Enter a number of pixels you want the resource area to be. this can always be updated by click/dragging the bar tot he right of the reesource names. this only applies to timeline resource view.
AjG.name: initresourceareasize

AjH.caption: Calendar Date Format
AjH.doc: Determines the text that will be displayed on the calendars column headings.  Takes any momentjs day formatting such as d, dd, ddd, dddd, ddd dd/yy
AjH.name: initcolumnheaderformat

AjI.caption: Date Dots
AjI.doc: When this box is checked, the following settings will override the calendars default current day display. Instead what will appear is a colored dot behind the date
AjI.name: initdatedots

AjL.caption: Click to Enter Day
AjL.doc: checking thisbox will make it so that when you click on a date, you enter that day.
AjL.name: initdayclickenterday

AIh.caption: Clicked Event Data
AIh.doc: This is an object containing Chosen Event Data
AIh.name: event_data

ARD.caption: Modified Event Data
ARD.doc: This is an object containing Modified Event Data
ARD.name: modifiedeventdata

AaR.caption: Selected TimeFrame Data
AaR.doc: This is an object containing Selected Time Frame Data
AaR.name: selected_timeframe_data

Aad.caption: Calendar Data
Aad.doc: This is an object containing Calendar Data
Aad.name: calendar_data
